Implement the actual LRU cache for compiled RegexQuery objects.

## Implementation Details
```rust
use parking_lot::RwLock;
use lru::LruCache;
use std::sync::Arc;

// Cache key: (field_name, pattern_string)
type RegexCacheKey = (String, String);

struct RegexCache {
    cache: RwLock<LruCache<RegexCacheKey, Arc<RegexQuery>>>,
}

impl RegexCache {
    fn new(capacity: usize) -> Self {
        Self {
            cache: RwLock::new(LruCache::new(
                std::num::NonZeroUsize::new(capacity).unwrap()
            )),
        }
    }

    fn get_or_insert(
        &self,
        field: &str,
        pattern: &str,
        build_fn: impl FnOnce() -> Result<RegexQuery>
    ) -> Result<Arc<RegexQuery>> {
        let key = (field.to_string(), pattern.to_string());

        // Fast path: read lock
        if let Some(cached) = self.cache.read().peek(&key) {
            return Ok(Arc::clone(cached));
        }

        // Slow path: build and insert
        let query = Arc::new(build_fn()?);
        self.cache.write().put(key, Arc::clone(&query));
        Ok(query)
    }
}
```

## Configuration
- Default capacity: 100 patterns
- Consider env var for tuning: `CASS_REGEX_CACHE_SIZE`
- Thread-safe with `parking_lot::RwLock` for minimal contention

## Integration Points
- Wire into TantivyIndex search methods
- Must not affect non-wildcard queries

## Rollback
Env var `CASS_REGEX_CACHE=0` bypasses cache entirely.

